{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dc4d49cb-9cb7-4048-9548-717aadcaf293","content":"Yes, you'll run into compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2 and .NET Core 3.1**, but it **dropped support for `net5.0`** since .NET 5 is out of support.\n\nHere's the breakdown for your target frameworks:\n\n| Framework | MSTest v3 Compatible? |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Yes |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ⚠️ Builds, but .NET Core 3.1 is end-of-life |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ No — not supported by MSTest v3 |\n\n**To migrate cleanly**, you should update `net5.0` to `net6.0` or later (preferably `net8.0`). You may also want to drop `netcoreapp3.1` in favor of a supported modern TFM.\n\nAlso note that MSTest v3 consolidates packages — you can replace both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` with the single **`MSTest`** meta-package (version 3.x).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1e70ab65-3227-49f7-9f04-92e8ff0f0743","outputTokens":273,"requestId":"BC21:2657C1:2129367:2506547:69FAA888"},"id":"31c47854-dc40-4394-801d-b3e2e3f7aac7","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:33:51.842Z","parentId":"247b1663-a8c6-495c-b39a-bb31cc5240ae"}
